Hoodlums in some communities withon Lagos State have taken to the street following President Muhammadu Buhari’s announcement, extending the initial two-week lockdown of Lagos, Ogun states and the FCT, Abuja by another 14 days, reports say. Information reaching LEADERSHIP inddicates these aggrieved youths have moved out to the streets in areas such as Shasha, Orisunbare, Idimu and Ejigbo. The development is a fallout to similar wave of attacks, robbery and looting being witnessed in Agege and some other areas in Lagos and neighbouring Ogun State recently.  Details Later …